A native  hash-based set where one value is reserved to mean "EMPTY" internally. The space overhead is fairly low
as there is only one power-of-two sized  to hold the values.  The set is re-hashed when adding a value that
would make it >= 75% full.  Consider extending and over-riding  if the values might be poor
hash keys; Lucene docids should be fine.
The internal fields are exposed publicly to enable more efficient use at the expense of better O-O principles.


To iterate over the integers held in this set, simply use code like this:

SentinelIntSet set = ...
foreach (int v in set.keys) 
{
    if (v == set.EmptyVal)
        continue;
    //use v...
}



NOTE: This was SentinelIntSet in Lucene


